                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony2-rest/edit/master/knpu/episode4/jwt-other-things.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Mostly, that's it! JWT authentication is pretty cool: create an endpoint
to <em>fetch</em> a token and an authenticator to check if that token is valid. With the
error handling we added, this is a <em>really</em> robust system.</p>
<p>But, there are a few other things I want you to think about: things that <em>you</em> may
want to consider for your situation.</p>
<h2 id="adding-scopes-roles-to-the-token">Adding Scopes/Roles to the Token <a class="headerlink" href="jwt-other-things#adding-scopes-roles-to-the-token" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>First, when we created our JWT, we put the username inside of it:</p>
