	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2723860034" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2723860034" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hi Ryan,<br>In security.yml, I noticed additional configuration:</p><p>access_control:<br>        - { path: ^/_wdt|_profiler, roles: IS_AUTHENTICATED_ANONYMOUSLY }<br>        - { path: ^/register, roles: IS_AUTHENTICATED_ANONYMOUSLY }<br>        - { path: ^/login, roles: IS_AUTHENTICATED_ANONYMOUSLY }<br>        # allow anonymous API - if auth is needed, it's handled in the controller<br>        - { path: ^/api, roles: IS_AUTHENTICATED_ANONYMOUSLY }<br>        - { path: ^/, roles: IS_AUTHENTICATED_FULLY }</p><p>Is this configuration related to the firewall?<br>Thanks!</p>
